com.amazonaws.mobileconnectors.s3.transfermanager.internal

Class CopyMonitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amazonaws.mobileconnectors.s3.transfermanager.internal.CopyMonitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TransferMonitor, java.util.concurrent.Callable<CopyResult>

    public class CopyMonitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.concurrent.Callable<CopyResult>, TransferMonitor
    Monitors an copy operation by periodically checking to see if the operation is completed, and returning a result if so. Otherwise, schedules a copy of itself to be run in the future. When waiting on the result of this class via a Future object, clients must call isDone() and getFuture()

      • getFuture

        public java.util.concurrent.Future<CopyResult> getFuture()
        Description copied from interface: TransferMonitor
        Returns a Future to wait on. Calling get() on this future will block while the transfer progress is checked, but its return does not guarantee the transfer is complete. Call isDone() to check for completion. Repeated calls to getFuture() can return different objects.
        Specified by:
